Warning: As this doesn't appear to be a bug with Tensorflow, the devs may ask for this to be moved to Stack Overflow.

Sounds like this is happening during the pip install tensorflow phase and you're unable to access the file. This is better off on Stack Overflow. In the meantime, please try one of the following:
(Assuming CPU)

Python 3.5
pip install https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Release/job/release-win/lastStableBuild/M=windows,PY=35/artifact/cmake_build/tf_python/dist/tensorflow-1.2.1-cp35-cp35m-win_amd64.whl

Python 3.6
pip install https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Release/job/release-win/lastStableBuild/M=windows,PY=36/artifact/cmake_build/tf_python/dist/tensorflow-1.2.1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl

EDIT: The S/O question is here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45081429/
If you decide to move this issue to Stack Overflow, please post the link here so that myself (or others that stumble upon this issue) can find the S/O thread.

_Warning: As this doesn't appear to be a bug with Tensorflow, the devs may ask for this to be moved to Stack Overflow._

Sounds like this is happening during the `pip install tensorflow` phase and you're unable to access the file. This is better off on Stack Overflow. In the meantime, please try one of the following:
(Assuming CPU)

**Python 3.5**
`pip install https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Release/job/release-win/lastStableBuild/M=windows,PY=35/artifact/cmake_build/tf_python/dist/tensorflow-1.2.1-cp35-cp35m-win_amd64.whl`

**Python 3.6**
`pip install https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Release/job/release-win/lastStableBuild/M=windows,PY=36/artifact/cmake_build/tf_python/dist/tensorflow-1.2.1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl`

EDIT: The S/O question is here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45081429/
~~If you decide to move this issue to Stack Overflow, please post the link here so that myself (or others that stumble upon this issue) can find the S/O thread.~~
